{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"4101a","heading":"Technical Mapping Advisory Council","label":"4101a Technical Mapping Advisory Council","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch50/schIII","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","CodificationSection was enacted as part of the Biggert-Waters Flood Insurance Reform Act of 2012, and also as part of the Moving Ahead for Progress in the 21st Century Act, also known as the MAP–21, and not as part of the National Flood Insurance Act of 1968 which comprises this chapter.","Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","DefinitionsFor definitions of terms used in this section, see .section 4004 of this title"],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Establishment","label":"a Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"There is established a council to be known as the Technical Mapping Advisory Council (in this section referred to as the “Council”).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Membership","label":"b Membership","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Administrator (or the designee thereof);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary of the Interior (or the designee thereof);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Secretary of Agriculture (or the designee thereof);","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the Under Secretary of Commerce for Oceans and Atmosphere (or the designee thereof); and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"E","heading":null,"label":"E","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized professional surveying association or organization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized professional mapping association or organization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized professional engineering association or organization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iv","heading":null,"label":"iv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/iv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized professional association or organization representing flood hazard determination firms;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"v","heading":null,"label":"v","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/v","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a representative of the United States Geological Survey;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vi","heading":null,"label":"vi","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/vi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fvi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a representative of a recognized professional association or organization representing State geographic information;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"vii","heading":null,"label":"vii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/vii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fvii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a representative of State national flood insurance coordination offices;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"viii","heading":null,"label":"viii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/viii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fviii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a representative of the Corps of Engineers;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ix","heading":null,"label":"ix","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/ix","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fix","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized regional flood and storm water management organization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"x","heading":null,"label":"x","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/x","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fx","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"2 representatives of different State government agencies that have entered into cooperating technical partnerships with the Administrator and have demonstrated the capability to produce flood insurance rate maps;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"xi","heading":null,"label":"xi","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/xi","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fxi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"2 representatives of different local government agencies that have entered into cooperating technical partnerships with the Administrator and have demonstrated the capability to produce flood insurance maps;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"xii","heading":null,"label":"xii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/xii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fxii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized floodplain management association or organization;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"xiii","heading":null,"label":"xiii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/xiii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fxiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a member of a recognized risk management association or organization; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"xiv","heading":null,"label":"xiv","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E/xiv","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/1/E","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F1%2FE%2Fxiv","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a State mitigation officer.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Qualifications","label":"2 Qualifications","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Members of the Council shall be appointed based on their demonstrated knowledge and competence regarding surveying, cartography, remote sensing, geographic information systems, or the technical aspects of preparing and using flood insurance rate maps. In appointing members under paragraph (1)(E), the Administrator shall, to the maximum extent practicable, ensure that the membership of the Council has a balance of Federal, State, local, tribal, and private members, and includes geographic diversity, including representation from areas with coastline on the Gulf of Mexico and other States containing areas identified by the Administrator as at high risk for flooding or as areas having special flood hazards.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"c","heading":"Duties","label":"c Duties","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"accuracy, general quality, ease of use, and distribution and dissemination of flood insurance rate maps and risk data; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"performance metrics and milestones required to effectively and efficiently map flood risk areas in the United States;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"flood insurance rate maps; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"data accuracy, data quality, data currency, and data eligibility;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recommend to the Administrator how to maintain, on an ongoing basis, flood insurance rate maps and flood risk identification;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":null,"label":"4","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recommend procedures for delegating mapping activities to State and local mapping partners;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":null,"label":"5","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/5/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F5%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"methods for improving interagency and intergovernmental coordination on flood mapping and flood risk determination; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/5/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/5","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F5%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a funding strategy to leverage and coordinate budgets and expenditures across Federal agencies; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":null,"label":"6","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a description of the activities of the Council;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"an evaluation of the status and performance of flood insurance rate maps and mapping activities to revise and update flood insurance rate maps, as required under ; andsection 4101b of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/c/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fc%2F6%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a summary of recommendations made by the Council to the Administrator.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"d","heading":"Future conditions risk assessment and modeling report","label":"d Future conditions risk assessment and modeling report","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"ensure that flood insurance rate maps incorporate the best available climate science to assess flood risks; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"the rise in the sea level; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/A/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FA%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"future development on flood risk; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"not later than 1 year after , prepare written recommendations in a future conditions risk assessment and modeling report and to submit such recommendations to the Administrator.July 6, 2012","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Responsibility of the Administrator","label":"2 Responsibility of the Administrator","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/d","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fd%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Administrator, as part of the ongoing program to review and update National Flood Insurance Program rate maps under , shall incorporate any future risk assessment submitted under paragraph (1)(B) in any such revision or update.section 4101b of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"e","heading":"Chairperson","label":"e Chairperson","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/e","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fe","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The members of the Council shall elect 1 member to serve as the chairperson of the Council (in this section referred to as the “Chairperson”).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"f","heading":"Coordination","label":"f Coordination","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/f","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Ff","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"To ensure that the Council’s recommendations are consistent, to the maximum extent practicable, with national digital spatial data collection and management standards, the Chairperson shall consult with the Chairperson of the Federal Geographic Data Committee (established pursuant to Office of Management and Budget Circular A–16).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"g","heading":"Compensation","label":"g Compensation","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/g","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fg","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Members of the Council shall receive no additional compensation by reason of their service on the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"h","heading":"Meetings and actions","label":"h Meetings and actions","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/h","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fh","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"In general","label":"1 In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/h/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fh%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Council shall meet not less frequently than twice each year at the request of the Chairperson or a majority of its members, and may take action by a vote of the majority of the members.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Initial meeting","label":"2 Initial meeting","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/h/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/h","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fh%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Administrator, or a person designated by the Administrator, shall request and coordinate the initial meeting of the Council.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"i","heading":"Officers","label":"i Officers","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Chairperson may appoint officers to assist in carrying out the duties of the Council under subsection (c).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"j","heading":"Staff","label":"j Staff","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/j","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fj","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"Staff of FEMA","label":"1 Staff of FEMA","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/j/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fj%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Upon the request of the Chairperson, the Administrator may detail, on a nonreimbursable basis, personnel of the Federal Emergency Management Agency to assist the Council in carrying out its duties.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"Staff of other Federal agencies","label":"2 Staff of other Federal agencies","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/j/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/j","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fj%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Upon request of the Chairperson, any other Federal agency that is a member of the Council may detail, on a nonreimbursable basis, personnel to assist the Council in carrying out its duties.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"k","heading":"Powers","label":"k Powers","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/k","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fk","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In carrying out this section, the Council may hold hearings, receive evidence and assistance, provide information, and conduct research, as it considers appropriate.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"l","heading":"Report to Congress","label":"l Report to Congress","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fl","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fl%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"recommendations made by the Council;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fl%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"actions taken by the Federal Emergency Management Agency to address such recommendations to improve flood insurance rate maps and flood risk data; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s4101a/l","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs4101a%2Fl%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"any recommendations made by the Council that have been deferred or not acted upon, together with an explanatory statement.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
